tool: ADD_CONTACT
description: Add contact to relationships with category/preferences.

tool: REMOVE_CONTACT
description: Remove contact from relationships.

tool: SCHEDULE_FOLLOW_UP
description: Schedule follow-up reminder for contact.

tool: SEARCH_CONTACTS
description: Search/list contacts by name or query.

tool: SEND_MESSAGE
description: send message via registered connector params target source targetKind message thread attachments urgency resolve exact/infer source contact/entity channel/room recent target connector hooks

tool: UPDATE_CONTACT
description: Update existing contact details.

tool: UPDATE_ENTITY
description: Edit contact details for person in conversation.

available_contexts: general

No prior conversation.

schedule a meeting with Alice and email her the agenda

message_handler: {"id":"message-handler:1778149693679","type":"message_handler","source":"message-service","createdAt":1778149693679,"metadata":{"processMessage":"RESPOND","plan":{"contexts":["calendar","email","contacts"]},"thought":"The user wants to schedule a meeting and send an email agenda. This requires calendar functionality to create the meeting and email functionality to send the agenda, plus contacts to retrieve Alice's email address. No direct reply is possible without using these tools, so we route to the appropriate contexts."}}

evaluator_stage:
task: Evaluate the just-executed action and route the next planner-loop step.

routes:
- FINISH: the task is complete or should stop
- NEXT_RECOMMENDED: one queued tool should run next before replanning
- CONTINUE: call the planner again because the queued plan is missing or stale

rules:
- evaluate the latest action result against the user's goal
- success means the user's requested outcome is fully evidenced by completed tool results, not merely planned
- never infer that a side effect happened unless a matching successful tool result exists
- if the user requested a write/send/save/create/update/delete/payment/transfer action and the only evidence is read/search/plan output, choose CONTINUE
- choose NEXT_RECOMMENDED only when one queued tool is clearly still grounded
- choose CONTINUE when the next step requires new planning
- messageToUser is optional progress, diagnosis, question, or final output
- copyToClipboard is optional and must include title and content
- thought is internal and not shown to the user

return:
JSON object only. No markdown, no prose, no XML, no legacy formats.

